# Link to this sectionHow to Test Computer Vision Models#

## Link to this sectionIntroduction#

Model testing checks how a [trained model](/guides/model-training-tips) performs on previously unseen, real-world data — moving, poorly lit, or partially hidden objects rather than a curated benchmark. While [model evaluation](/guides/model-evaluation-insights) measures metrics on a labeled dataset, testing verifies that the model's learned behavior matches the [goals of your application](/guides/defining-project-goals) before deployment. This guide covers preparing test data, testing Ultralytics YOLO26 models, and catching [overfitting](https://www.ultralytics.com/glossary/overfitting), underfitting, and data leakage.

  


  
